   <br></br>
   <h1>What They Should Do</h1>
   <br></br> 
   Different image search engines behave in different ways, but all have a
common theme when searching for images.
<br><br>
Ideally, an image search engine would have the following features
<font color="red">*</font>
<ul>
   <li>Allow keyword searching of image content, date, and creator</li>
   <li>Let you search by color, shape, and other formal attributes</li>
   <li>Search databases internal to a site</li>
   <li>Display the image as part of your search results</li>
   <li>Allow you to find the rights-holder</li>
   <li>Furnish the rights status and terms for licensing</li>
</ul>
<br><br>
<font color="red">* <a
href="http://www.onlineinc.com/onlinemag/OL1998/berinstein5.html">Berinstein,
Paula. <u>Turning Visual: Image Search
Engines on the Web</u></a></font>
</font>
